This paper deals with the analysis of temporal hashtag usage patterns in Twitter and proposes a cognitive-inspired hashtag recommendation algorithm. The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques and natural language processing to analyze Twitter data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
